---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Toyb"
  description="Placeholder privacy policy for Toyb with standard sections on processing purposes and user rights."
>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      This page is a professional placeholder and must be reviewed by qualified
      counsel before production use. It is not legal advice.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Controller and Contact</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Controller: Toyb (placeholder entity name).</li>
      <li>Contact email: privacy@toyb.space (placeholder mailbox).</li>
      <li>Postal contact: to be defined in final corporate imprint.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Collected</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Identity and account details (name, email, role).</li>
      <li>Usage data (pages viewed, session events, diagnostics).</li>
      <li>Communication data (support requests, feedback forms).</li>
      <li>Technical data (IP logs, browser and device metadata).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Purpose of Processing</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide and maintain core service functionality.</li>
      <li>Protect service security, integrity, and abuse prevention.</li>
      <li>Improve product quality and user experience.</li>
      <li>Respond to support and legal compliance obligations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Lawful Basis</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Performance of a contract for account and service delivery.</li>
      <li>
        Legitimate interests for security, diagnostics, and service improvement.
      </li>
      <li>
        Consent for optional analytics or marketing processing where applicable.
      </li>
      <li>
        Legal obligation where retention or disclosure is required by law.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Account data: retained while account is active and for a defined
        post-closure period.
      </li>
      <li>
        Support records: retained according to operational and compliance needs.
      </li>
      <li>
        Security logs: retained for a limited period unless extended for
        investigations.
      </li>
      <li>Consent records: retained as long as needed to prove compliance.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>User Rights</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Right of access, rectification, erasure, and restriction of processing.
      </li>
      <li>Right to object to processing based on legitimate interests.</li>
      <li>Right to data portability where applicable.</li>
      <li>
        Right to withdraw consent at any time when processing is consent-based.
      </li>
      <li>
        Right to lodge a complaint with the relevant supervisory authority.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>International Transfers</h2>
    <p>
      If personal data is transferred across jurisdictions, appropriate
      safeguards should be applied, such as contractual clauses or equivalent
      mechanisms.
    </p>

    <h2>Policy Updates</h2>
    <p>
      This placeholder may change as operational requirements evolve. Update the
      effective date and legal text before public release.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
